crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The Perl script performs a ping sweep across a specified IP address range.  It takes a user-supplied IP range (e.g., 192.168.1.1-254) as input.  The script then iterates through each IP address in that range, using the `Net::Ping` module to send ICMP echo requests (pings). For each IP address, it records whether the ping was successful (host online) or not (host offline), measuring response time if successful. The results, including the response time for online hosts, are printed to the console and written to a file named "report.txt". The script also calculates and displays the total time taken for the entire ping sweep.  No remote file downloads are performed.
